  "title": "Zombies, Inc.",
  "description": "Zombies roam Manhattan. Ray’s still chasing commissions. Trapped inside New York’s iconic Rockefeller Plaza, one desperate jeweler battles the undead, late capitalism, and his unraveling dreams. A darkly funny solo musical with a killer score, ZOMBIES, INC. asks: what’s worth dying for—and what’s worth waking up to?",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Marcus Perkins Bejarano, Kim Jinhyoung<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Devanand Janki MUSIC DIR Ryan Sigurdson<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Damon Pitcher<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Phoenix McLeod<br/>",
  "website": "https://liveandincolor.org | @theatreincolor | zombies-inc.com | @zombiesinc.musical",
  "plain_language": "ZOMBIES, INC. is a one-person musical about Ray, who works in a New York jewelry store. When a zombie apocalypse begins, he gets stuck at work but still dreams about his future. Through songs and funny stories, Ray wonders if he was already living like a zombie before everything changed. The show is about love, loneliness, and what it means to be alive.",
